    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Dimorphanthes coronopifolia are antimicrobial, anti-inflammatory, and antioxidant. The plant's antimicrobial properties help combat various infections by inhibiting the growth of pathogenic microorganisms. The presence of saponins, flavonoids, and volatile oils in Dimorphanthes coronopifolia contributes to its anti-inflammatory effects, which alleviate symptoms of conditions such as arthritis and reduce swelling. Additionally, the antioxidant properties of the plant's bioactive compounds, including flavonoids and phenolic acids, protect against oxidative stress and cell damage. The anti-cancer properties of Dimorphanthes coronopifolia have also been observed in various studies, where the plant's bioactive compounds have shown the ability to inhibit the growth of cancer cells and induce apoptosis.",
