    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Dimorphanthes coronopifolia are flavonoids, saponins, and phenolic compounds, which contribute to its medicinal properties. Flavonoids present in the plant have antioxidant and anti-inflammatory activities, which may help in reducing oxidative stress and inflammation in the body. Saponins, on the other hand, have been found to possess antimicrobial properties, which may aid in treating infections and wounds. Phenolic compounds, including gallic acid and ferulic acid, have been reported to exhibit antioxidant and anti-inflammatory activities, further supporting the plant's medicinal potential. The combination of these bioactive compounds in Dimorphanthes coronopifolia may contribute to its use in traditional medicine for treating various ailments.",
