    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Dimorphanthes coronopifolia are infusion, tea, tincture, salve, and decoction. Infusions are made by steeping the leaves or flowers in hot water, while decoctions are made by boiling the roots or bark to release their medicinal properties. The tea preparation involves steeping the leaves or flowers in boiling water for a shorter duration, while the tincture is a concentrated liquid extract made by soaking the plant material in a solvent such as ethanol or glycerin. Salves are topical preparations made by infusing the plant material in a carrier oil, which can be used to treat skin conditions. These preparations are used to treat various ailments, including fever, digestive issues, and skin conditions, due to the plant's antimicrobial and anti-inflammatory properties.",
